<br>
People who want something will not respect other people's rights or feelings at all in-game. They will take what they want unless there are more people who say &quot;You can't have it now&quot; than there are who will take it without permission. When Karana players and guilds alike can reach a consensus over mobs the minute they get there, without being concerned over getting their epic first, or completing their set of uber armor, THEN the KGC will no longer be needed. <br>
<br>
In other words, never. <br>
<br>
The leaders of guilds on Karana have decided that they wish to sacrifice their time to tracking rotations as opposed to fighting tooth and nail every minute something pops. It is a tradeoff. Every once in a while, some dickhead with an agenda like Zfalcon or Dazzadi comes along and tries to mess with the KGC, for no other reason than to stir shit up because he likes it when people get mad. Unfortunately, he dupes a number of people into following him, people who eventually figure out that they've made pariahs of themselves with most of the guilds on the server and gotten nothing good for it.  <p>Haemish MacLennan<br>
Founder<Br>
Karana Council of Guilds<br>
